# Kotlin Conventions

## Style & Formatting

- Formatting rules and editor settings are in `.editorconfig`. Kotlinter enforces them.
- Compiler options (warnings-as-errors, extra warnings, etc.) are in the convention plugins under `build-logic/`.
- Run `./gradlew lintKotlin` to check, `./gradlew formatKotlin` to fix.

## API Visibility

- Published libraries use `explicitApi()` — every public declaration needs an explicit `public` modifier.
- Use `internal` for implementation details; prefer `private` when the symbol doesn't leave the file.
- Cross-module internals use `@InternalKrayonApi` (from `core`). Modules that consume it opt in via `languageSettings.optIn(...)` in Gradle.

## Patterns

- Prefer `@JvmInline value class` for lightweight type-safe wrappers (see `Color`).
- Use `expect`/`actual` for platform-specific code.
- Use `contract { }` blocks (`@OptIn(ExperimentalContracts::class)`) for scope functions that callers depend on (e.g. `withClip`, `withTransform`).
- Common test code goes in `commonTest` with `kotlin("test")` and `kotlinx-coroutines-test`.

## Source Set Hierarchy

The default KMP hierarchy template is applied. The `compose` module adds a custom `skiaMain` source set shared by JVM/Apple/JS/Wasm targets.
